td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udramadon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dramadon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/02 11:31:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> Neutrality does not give you permission to be cruel. In fact cruelity is obsolete if all you want is to gain power. Being cruel means taking time away from what your goal apparently is, to become the most powerful. While you are busy taking time committing genocide and forcing migrations in the name of Solusek Ro and neutrality (?), other people are quietly becoming much more powerful because they are not wasting time trying to become an anti-christ (or whatever the Norrathian equivalent is). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/02 11:39:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> You misunderstand what cruelty is. The cruelty that you describe is the evil form of cruelty:  hunting people down and being cruel for the sake of being cruel. The cruelty that is acceptable to the Great Lord is cruelty that serves the purpose of amassing power.<br>
<br>
For example.<br>
You are a ruler of a rather unruly village. Do you leave them to plot against your back, causing your power to deteriorate? Or do you suppress the population to the point that they have no time to plot, therebye not only preserving your power over them, but increasing your hold on their hearts?<br>
<br>
A follower of Solusek would do the latter not because it would cause suffering, but because it would increase his power. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uatelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atelen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/Paris/LeftBank/4815/pics/dinovisn.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gold Medal in the<BR>Distance Gnome Punt</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/02 12:58:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> You are a ruler of a rather unruly village. Do you leave them to plot against your back, causing your power to deteriorate? Or do you suppress the population to the point that they have no time to plot, therebye not only preserving your power over them, but increasing your hold on their hearts?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes... until they rise up and kill you while laughing. Hitler tried this one Eamin, it didn't work for him.<br>
<br>
Option #3: Work with the people to figure out what it is they want, thereby gaining respect and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> lasting</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> power in the community. This doesn't mean don't keep a firm hand; dissidents should still be punished, but a well-liked leader will last a lot longer than a cruel one, no matter what their aims.<br>
<br>
Unless you have a chanter charming the whole villiage... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomish Advocate</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/02 2:18:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> Eamin, you're a fool. Fortunately, you don't have the power to be a dangerous fool. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/02 6:42:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=51>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> No, Whizbang, I think you are the fool. So stuck in the rut of goodness, so mired in sentimentality and pity and compassion that you reject anything more balanced than it. While civil war rages in Ak`Anon, you still trumpet the gnomish race's &quot;superiority.&quot;<br>
<br>
And Atelen, your solution allows for but one outcome:  someone more powerful will sieze control of the city. Sentimentality has never ruled a lasting society. Look at the Combine, once great but now two squabbling factions. Look at the elves, once great but now nothing more than shades inhabiting an ancient forest, with no influence on world affairs due to the ruthlessness of the Great Lord.<br>
<br>
Now look at the ruthless:<br>
The Teir`Dal society has built itself on cruelty, and it remains one of the most influential forces in the Old World centuries after its founding.<br>
Look at the giants, within a very short timespan they ascended from primitive savages to a powerful force on the frozen continent on the heels of their cruelty.<br>
Look at Sanctus Seru, a city far more orderly and safe than its counterpart due to its ruthless crushing of dissent in the name of GOOD.<br>
<br>
Whether used by good or evil or neutrality, cruelty builds powerful societies.<br>
No great sentimental empire exists.<br>
Many a great ruthless empire exists.<br>
If our goal is power, it seems to me that mercilessness is the path to it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uatelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atelen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/Paris/LeftBank/4815/pics/dinovisn.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gold Medal in the<BR>Distance Gnome Punt</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/02 6:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> Certainly, the tier'dal civilization is built on cruelty, but they revel in it. It's the same thing as saying another civilization was built on happiness.<br>
<br>
I have never visited the giants, nor explored Sanctus Seru, so I do not feel myself knowledgable enough to comment on that.<br>
<br>
Societies built by a leader's cruelty against the people do not last long. The only stable ones, as you pointed out, are the ones that accept cruelty and oppression. so sure, if you took control of a band of fanatics, they wouldn't mind, because they'd be happy, unless of course they were just as ruthless, in which case you'd be thrown out and/or silenced.<br>
<br>
Neutrality can seem cruel on occassion, but it never uses cruelty consistently. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/02 11:16:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=53>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> Those who handicap themselves in the manner you suggest, Atelen, are throwing away potential paths to power. Saying &quot;I shall not be cruel because it is evil&quot; is isolating yourself from the power you could gain by being cruel and merciless. This is counterproductive and foolish.<br>
The Great Lord advises gaining power in ANY WAY POSSIBLE. If this means slaughtering an entire village to recover an artifact that they wouldn't give up without a fight, slaughter the damn village. If you let your sentimentality and &quot;morals&quot; get in the way of gaining power, you are not following the words of Ro. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomish Advocate</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/02 11:28:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The Great Lord advises gaining power in ANY WAY POSSIBLE.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Prove it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/02 11:32:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> &quot;The Followers of Solusek Ro believe in the raw and unbridled power of fire. Fire created the world and in fire shall it be consumed. True aggressive action is the only way for one to obtain what is desired. Power is gained by superior force. Followers of Ro have little fear. They are bold and brash, say what they mean and do what they say. Social graces are something they neither possess nor desire. They demand the respect of their peers and more often than not, earn it as well. Those who seek true elemental power follow Solusek Ro, and thus many Wizards turn to his burning embrace.&quot;<br>
<br>
TRUE AGGRESSIVE ACTION IS THE ONLY WAY FOR ONE TO OBTAIN WHAT IS DESIRED.<br>
POWER IS GAINED BY SUPERIOR FORCE.<br>
<br>
In other words:<br>
<br>
Do anything that will get you power, no matter how immoral or aggressive. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Gnomish Advocate</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/6/02 11:35:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm38.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/flappy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ERUDITES &gt; ALL</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> TRUE AGGRESSIVE ACTION IS THE ONLY WAY FOR ONE TO OBTAIN WHAT IS DESIRED.<br>
POWER IS GAINED BY SUPERIOR FORCE.<br>
<br>
In other words:<br>
<br>
